<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 14 at 3:15PM CDT  by NWS San Angelo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Nolan
and northwestern Taylor Counties through 400 PM CDT...
At 314 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Camp Butman, or 8 miles south of Trent. This storm was nearly
stationary.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Merkel and Camp Butman.
This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 256 and 257.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
